1lx.title: Reads algebra
1lx.clickbait: Do you have sufficient mathematical ability that you can read a sentence that uses some algebra or invokes a mathematical idea, without slowing down too much?
1lx.text: This requisite asks whether you can read a sentence that throws in algebra or a mathematical concept, without slowing down too much.  For instance, a sentence remarking that in the limit of independently flipping N coins with a 1/N probability of coming up heads, the chance of never getting heads is 1/*e*.  If that *kind* of sentence is one you can read, you should mark yourself as understanding this requisite, so you will automatically be shown Arbital pages and tabs that invoke math of that level.
